name: phenylacetate---CoA ligase
reaction: ATP + phenylacetate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + phenylacetyl-CoA [RN:R02539]
comment: Also acts, more slowly, on acetate, propanoate and butanoate, but not on hydroxy derivatives of phenylacetate and related compounds.

references.title: Purification and biochemical characterization of phenylacetyl-CoA ligase from Pseudomonas putida. A specific enzyme for the catabolism of phenylacetic acid.
